doc.previous: Both trails lead to spectacular views of the surrounding areas,[65] but have inherent dangers as well. The thick andesite caps are heavily eroded, leaving tall crumbling columns near their edges. At least six people have fallen from the Table Rocks since 2006,[68][69] including a man from Central Point who tumbled through a rock shaft on Lower Table Rock to his death in May 2007 and was not found for over nineteen months.[70] Another man from Murray, Utah fell 200 feet (61Â m) from Lower Table Rock and died in September 2009.[68]
